<subSubSection id="9F6EA60A9FFCC31836BF1886D1F37669" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="type locality">
<paragraph id="6D6D402037C585D429C12C062A390695" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Type locality.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4BF44450A14B71C09FB04DE01078C943" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Germany, Eifel, Totenmaar, 22.2.1974.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2A060565F8E381D21360758D63948DAB" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Valvae dorsiventral, dorsal margin broadly convex, ventral margin straight; ends not protracted, rounded, or subrostrate to rostrate; length 21.5-41.0 
<normalizedToken id="2D93779F7ECAFD1FF2F92594DF98FD1C" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, breadth 8.0-11.0 
<normalizedToken id="579B6CA3E86A28B0A7DF4FE91AC57864" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, L/B ratio 2.7-4.0; axial area narrow, linear-arched, indistinct central area; striae 9-13 in 10 
<normalizedToken id="BF6CD6E74D78FA160B7A0BA28153809D" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, becoming 11-14 toward ends, one isolated pore at end of central striae on ventral side; 22-27 punctae in 10 
<normalizedToken id="B038DB3EB222C22493004B1F99CB7217" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="877114982D7D3EF2C347754E1F925F7C" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="5F3AAD46253CC0CCE858F248250B6E6C" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8EFCC1338127709B0EBBBDD7B088DA2A" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
The combination of 
<taxonomicName id="C32C7374B631740BE584F4C01A395067" authority="" authorityName="Krammer" authorityYear="2002" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Cymbellaceae" genus="Cymbella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cymbella excisa subsp. var. var. procera" order="Cymbellales" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="variety" species="excisa" subSpecies="var." variety="procera">Cymbella excisa var. procera</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="41D2DC9CB2AE69DEB6CBD308597D7158" authority="" authorityName="Kuetz" authorityYear="1844" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Cymbellaceae" genus="Cymbella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cymbella affinis" order="Cymbellales" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis id="03C0C966E45096FEE9B64C54B9DB34D7" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Cymbella affinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
would be illegitimate unless it was given a new name, because it would be a later homonym of 
<taxonomicName id="8813E27C7B77C23794602732ACB26A84" authority="" authorityName="Krammer" authorityYear="2002" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Cymbellaceae" genus="Cymbella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cymbella affinis subsp. var. var. procera" order="Cymbellales" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="variety" species="affinis" subSpecies="var." variety="procera">Cymbella affinis var. procera</taxonomicName>
Krammer. Specimens designated by 
<bibRefCitation id="BE974C02C360EEBEDD2D20CA6A6BA053" author="Krammer, K" journalOrPublisher="Diatoms of Europe" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="1 - 584" refId="B7" refString="Krammer, K, 2002. Diatoms of the European inland waters and comparable habitats. Cymbella. Diatoms of Europe 3: 1 - 584" title="Diatoms of the European inland waters and comparable habitats. Cymbella." volume="3" year="2002">Krammer (2002)</bibRefCitation>
, i.e., the preparation 212A IOK (BRM), were found to belong to more than one taxon therefore to clarify the taxonomy we designated a lectotype as established in Art. 9.11 of the ICN (
<bibRefCitation id="E86C44EA2B107B5F0D711F1F56B0B4C1" author="McNeill, J" journalOrPublisher="Koeltz Scientific Books, Koenigstein" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="1 - 240" refId="B14" refString="McNeill, J, Barrie, FR, Buck, WR, Demoulin, V, Greuter, W, Hawksworth, DL, Herendeen, PS, Knapp, S, Marhold, K, Prado, J, Prud'Homme Van Reine, WF, Smith, GF, Wiersema, JH, Turland, NJ, 2012. International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Melbourne Code) adopted by the Eighteenth International Botanical Congress Melbourne, Australia, July 2011. Koeltz Scientific Books, Koenigstein: 1 - 240" title="International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Melbourne Code) adopted by the Eighteenth International Botanical Congress Melbourne, Australia, July 2011" year="2012">McNeill et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="49B542C8D9FC645EB4677E2F6B772026" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
A broader range of metric characteristics were highlighted in this study compared to the characterization of the type population (
<bibRefCitation id="9389900306D6AB5565C4B8BCFD0B49F3" author="Krammer, K" journalOrPublisher="Diatoms of Europe" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="1 - 584" refId="B7" refString="Krammer, K, 2002. Diatoms of the European inland waters and comparable habitats. Cymbella. Diatoms of Europe 3: 1 - 584" title="Diatoms of the European inland waters and comparable habitats. Cymbella." volume="3" year="2002">Krammer 2002</bibRefCitation>
, p. 28). We find smaller (21.5-41.0 vs. 24-41 
<normalizedToken id="7446314C8C32C6AAA450205B3C3D729D" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
) and narrower (8.0-11.0 vs. 8.4-11.0 
<normalizedToken id="216A9481C2A873D08522F3FA31168B62" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
) representatives of this taxon compared to the 
<bibRefCitation id="D3462DD96531ED820B47E1C84305F97A" author="Krammer, K" journalOrPublisher="Diatoms of Europe" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="1 - 584" refId="B7" refString="Krammer, K, 2002. Diatoms of the European inland waters and comparable habitats. Cymbella. Diatoms of Europe 3: 1 - 584" title="Diatoms of the European inland waters and comparable habitats. Cymbella." volume="3" year="2002">
<normalizedToken id="44F3602844A3B5CEA9871961FE034E1E" originalValue="Krammer’s">Krammer's</normalizedToken>
(2002)
</bibRefCitation>
records. Still considering 
<bibRefCitation id="8DB0A3215998C606605403E797479A79" author="Krammer, K" journalOrPublisher="Diatoms of Europe" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="1 - 584" refId="B7" refString="Krammer, K, 2002. Diatoms of the European inland waters and comparable habitats. Cymbella. Diatoms of Europe 3: 1 - 584" title="Diatoms of the European inland waters and comparable habitats. Cymbella." volume="3" year="2002">
<normalizedToken id="FACABD4477A487E8B6878940DF04C5CA" originalValue="Krammer’s">Krammer's</normalizedToken>
(2002)
</bibRefCitation>
findings, we observe more densely striated (9-13 vs. 9-11 striae in 10 
<normalizedToken id="FFB71855FB6DC6B695EF8F43CC1048B1" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
) and less punctate (22-27 vs. 24-27 punctae in 10 
<normalizedToken id="9AF48C4407F13D26C8AF62BE55ECFEDC" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
) valves.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
